"Suburgatory" follows 16-year-old Tess (Jane Levy) who, after getting caught with condoms in her drawer, 
is forced by her single father George (Jeremy Sisto) to move to the suburbs, a small town where all the moms are fake and so are the other teenagers at school. 
When George tells one mother that he is not married, it sets off a chain reaction of mothers introducing their daughters to Tess and "themselves" to George. 
At the first day of school, Tessa is a little scared to be going into a world of big-haired, fake-boobed mothers and Red Bull-chugging children, but slowly she and George as well find a way to survive and get along.
